  "prompt": "Is white an actual color?",
  "response": "The concept of color can be complex and varies depending on the context. In the context of light and physics, white is considered a color because it is the result of combining all visible wavelengths of light. When light encompasses all wavelengths in the visible spectrum, it appears white to the human eye.\n\nHowever, in the context of pigments and dyes (such as in painting or printing), white is not typically considered a true color because it does not result from the absorption and reflection of specific wavelengths. Instead, white pigment or dye reflects all wavelengths of light.\n\nSo, whether or not white is considered an actual color depends on the perspective\u2014whether you are talking about light or pigments.",
